    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-07-06T18:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-07-06T18:37:00-05:00" n="671"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2353: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d671fn1">This telegram, drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, was repeated to Tokyo for <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CGMW1"
                            >Clark</persName> as telegram 51 and to Pusan as telegram 17.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-07-06T19:37:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1953—7:37 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. For <persName corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> from Secretary. Have
                    carefully considered your #19<note n="2" xml:id="d671fn2">Dated July 6, <ref
                            target="#pg_1336">p. 1336</ref>.</note> and 061600Z.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d671fn3">Dated July 7, <ref target="#pg_1337">p. 1337</ref>.</note>
                    President’s June 16 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] letter<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d671fn4">Not printed; for text, see <hi rend="italic">Public Papers
                            of the Presidents of the United States: <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                                >Dwight D. Eisenhower</persName>, 1953</hi>, pp. 377–380.</note>
                    offering security pact was informally cleared with Senate leaders and received
                    general public approval. Any present uncertainty as to Senate action is slight
                    and results from feeling in some quarters that President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> desires to commit US to a reckless suicide
                    pact. We are trying to eliminate this fear and I shall be meeting early Tuesday
                    with bipartisan Senate leaders and will then cable further. What is needed most
                    of all is for <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> to give assurance that
                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> is dependable partner not committed to
                    rash adventures.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
